author: Paul Pack C-H sports editor
title: Lexington battles York
text:
Lexington battles York Paul Pack C-H sports editor lexch.com | 0 comments 
LEXINGTON, Neb. – Twelve seconds into the game against York, Lexington was behind, 6-0. 
York player JJ Schulz would take Lexington’s kickoff back for six, and Jorre Luther would nail the PAT. 
Lexington’s scoring drought, 90-0, was broken by Josh White in the fourth quarter from 39 yards out to put Lexington on the board and avoiding another shutout. 
Lexington ended the game with 202 total yards, 146 in the air, 56 on the ground. 
York would rack up 427 total yards, 22 in the air, 205 on the ground. 
Final score was 36-6.
